Class MySymbolTable<SymbolType,RecordType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • MySymbolTable<SymbolType,RecordType>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SymbolTable<SymbolType,RecordType>

    public class MySymbolTable<SymbolType,RecordType>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SymbolTable<SymbolType,RecordType>
    Author:
    Jimmy Botero CS310 Spring 2018 Project 4 George Mason University File Name: MySymbolTable.java Description: Maintains the table for unique symbols (addresses) from a sequence of references. In the pair SymbolType represents different symbols and RecordType defines the record of each symbol (address), in our case the last access time.
